This paper focuses on analyzing the dynamics of collective attention in Twitter, which involves social interactions, natural language processing, and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
